claim.claim-text:
1. A method of preparing a hydrogel having a low elasticity modulus from a hydrophilic polymer, comprising the steps of:
(a) selecting a hydrophilic polymer of sufficiently high molecular weight, wherein the hydrophilic polymer has a hydroxyl group-carrying carbon-carbon backbone;
(b) dissolving said polymer in a solvent to a concentration not exceeding about 5% (wt);
(c) adding a crosslinking agent;
(d) mixing and reacting the polymer with the crosslinking agent; and
(e) evaporating said solvent; and
(f) optionally adding water.

8. A method of preparing a hydrogel having a low elasticity modulus from a hydrophilic polymer, comprising the steps of:
(a) selecting hydrophilic polymer of sufficiently high molecular weight, wherein the hydrophilic polymer has a hydroxyl group-carrying carbon-carbon backbone;
(b) dissolving said polymer in a solvent to a concentration not exceeding about 5% (wt);
(c) adding a crosslinking agent;
(d) mixing and reacting the polymer with the crosslinking agent; and
(e) evaporating said solvent; and
(f) optionally adding water,

11. A method of preparing a hydrogel having a low elasticity modulus from a hydrophilic polymer, comprising the steps of:
(a) selecting a hydrophilic polymer of sufficiently high molecular weight;
(b) dissolving said polymer in a solvent to a concentration not exceeding about 5% (wt);
(c) adding a diisocyanate crosslinking agent;
(d) mixing and reacting the polymer with the crosslinking agent; and
(e) evaporating said solvent; and
(f) optionally adding water.

12. A method of preparing a hydrogel having a low elasticity modulus from a hydrophilic (poly(1-hydroxy-1,3-propanediyl)) polymer, comprising the steps of:
(a) selecting a hydrophilic (poly(1-hydroxy-1,3-propanediyl)) polymer of sufficiently high molecular weight;
(b) dissolving said polymer in a solvent to a concentration not exceeding about 5% (wt);
(c) adding a crosslinking agent;
(d) mixing and reacting the polymer with the crosslinking agent; and
(e) evaporating said solvent; and
(f) optionally adding water.
